1.Roads and libraries

  Determine the min cost to provide library access to all citizens of HackerLand.

  There are n cities numbered from 1 to n.

  Currently no libraries and cities not connected.

  Bidirectional roads may be built between any city pair listed.

  A citizen can access a library if :

  Their city contains a library.

  They can travel by road from their city to a city containing a library.


  Meaning spanning tree with a condition.


  Meaning ==> 


  How to have all nodes satisfied.





